Update your vehicle-estimate.css with these overrides (specific to Stock Coded Parts popup):

/* Ensure form rows stretch to popup width */
.scparts-popup-style .form-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); /* 3 equal columns */
    gap: 16px;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    width: 100%; /* ✅ stretch full container width */
}

/* Make each form group take full width of its column */
.scparts-popup-style .form-group {
    width: 100%;
}

/* Force all Kendo inputs to use full width of their parent */
.scparts-popup-style .k-textbox,
.scparts-popup-style .k-combobox,
.scparts-popup-style .k-numerictextbox,
.scparts-popup-style .k-datepicker,
.scparts-popup-style input,
.scparts-popup-style select {
    width: 100% !important;   /* ✅ expand inside column */
    box-sizing: border-box;
}

✅ Section Titles Full Width

Right now your section titles (e.g. Part Information, Supplier Information) are just inline divs. To make them span the full popup:

.scparts-popup-style .section-title {
    grid-column: span 3;   /* ✅ force to take full width */
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: bold;
    margin: 16px 0 8px;
}

✅ Example: Cleaned Up Part Information Section

In StockCodedPartsModel.cshtml, make sure it looks like this (no inline widths):

<div class="section-title">Part Information</div>
<div class="form-row">
    <div class="form-group">
        @Html.LabelFor(m => m.MMSStockCode, "Stock Code", new { @class = "form-label required-label" })
        @Html.EditorFor(m => m.MMSStockCode, "ScComboBox", new { htmlAttributes = new { required = "required" } })
    </div>
    <div class="form-group">
        @Html.LabelFor(m => m.PartType, "Part Type", new { @class = "form-label" })
        @(Html.Kendo().TextBoxFor(m => m.PartType).HtmlAttributes(new { @readonly = "readonly" }))
    </div>
    <div class="form-group">
        @Html.LabelFor(m => m.UnitCost, "Unit Cost", new { @class = "form-label" })
        @(Html.Kendo().NumericTextBoxFor(m => m.UnitCost).Format("c2"))
    </div>
</div>
